  <div> <span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;">Hi {{{Recipient.FirstName}}},</span></span> 
   <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;">I wanted to reach out and see how you are, I know this is an overwhelming time for most.&nbsp;</span></span></p> 
   <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;">The progression of COVID-19 across Canada has reshaped our daily life, including how we communicate and interact. <b>Hygiene practices have been redefined, and as a result many people have adopted new habits in hopes of limiting their exposure to the virus.</b> Commonly, many people are now taking proactive measures to protect their health by wearing personal protective equipment (PPE), including gloves and masks. </span><span style="font-family:&quot;Century Gothic&quot;,sans-serif"> </span></span></p> 
   <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;">In hopes of limiting individual’s exposure to the virus, many businesses and facilities have now added increased health measures including more frequent disinfection and sanitizing practices. However, with an increased amount of people wearing PPE in public, <u>the disposal of these items should be cautioned</u>. Without a proper disposal outlet in place, many individuals are simply leaving their PPE in the garbage. As a result, anyone who encounters used PPE, such as patrons or janitors are then at <i>risk to being exposed to COVID-19</i>. <b>It is estimated that COVID-19 can live on surfaces for up to 72 hours.</b></span><b><span style="font-family:&quot;Century Gothic&quot;,sans-serif"> </span></b></span></p> 
   <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;">In hospitals, contaminated articles are properly disposed of separately from standard garbage. In order to minimize the spread of COVID-19 facilities must address their patrons’ habits, which includes where they dispose of PPE. <b>To&nbsp;prepare businesses to return to work, the World Health Organization has recommended separate closed receptacles to dispose of used PPE.</b></span><b><span style="font-family:&quot;Century Gothic&quot;,sans-serif"> </span></b></span></p> 
   <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;">As an industry leader, I wanted to let you know <b>Citron Hygiene is now able to provide PPE disposal services</b>. During each service, our certified technician will thoroughly <i>disinfect</i> the disposal unit using a <i>DIN approved chemical</i> and, safely take the waste off site for proper disposal. </span><span style="font-family:&quot;Century Gothic&quot;,sans-serif"> </span></span></p> 
   <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;">I would like to help you ensure the safety of your patrons and staff. I would like to set up a call to further explain our service, and how it can help protect your business. Please let me know if you have any questions. I look forward to hearing from you.</span></span></p> 
   <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;">Thank you,</span></span></p> <span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;"> {{{Sender.Name}}}</span></span> 
   <br /> 
